discourse_list.title: Introducing: Protocol Engineering Weekly Office Hours!

content.content: The Protocol Engineering Team will hold a weekly Office Hours for anyone to drop in and ask smart contract related questions. These sessions will be run as an informal format with the primary goal of helping participants in MakerDAO to better understand Maker smart contracts. Sessions will not be recorded. This meeting takes place weekly Tuesdays at 15:00 UTC. Google Meet joining info Video call link: https://meet.google.com/dic-upmx-ipt Or dial: ‪(US) +1 318-433-2148‬ PIN: ‪927 491 303‬# More phone numbers: https://tel.meet/dic-upmx-ipt?pin=4422665651267 Please come with technical questions or topics in mind! See the MakerDAO Community Calendar for more topics.

I will hopefully be dropping by to ask first-glance opinions on this first draft of a proposal. I’d like to know if it makes sense to pursue a more polished version and how much time would have to be diverted to get something launched back half of the year. Talk to y’all tomorrow!
